{
  "text": "is a triangle equivalence, and hence by [CITATION_1] Lemma 3.9] , Γ is homologically smooth too. By Lemma 2.2, per(Γ) ⊇ D fd (Γ). It is clear that Γ satisfies the conditions (P1) and (P2) in Lemma 3.12 and it follows that D fd (Γ) has a silting object. As D fd (Γ) = per(Γ) chf by Lemma 2.6, it follows that D b (coh(X)) chf has a silting object. By [CITATION_2] Proposition 7.47] , there is a fully faithful triangle functor",
